BNB uses an Auto-Burn system to reduce its total supply to 100,000,000 BNB. The BNB Auto-Burn mechanism adjusts the amount of BNB to be burned based on BNB's price and the number of blocks generated on BNB Smart Chain (BSC) during the quarter. This offers greater transparency and predictability to the BNB community.
BNB lost in eligible cases can also be reimbursed through the BNB Pioneer Burn Program. This counts users' lost coins towards the official burn count and reimburses them with BNB.
BNB additionally uses a real-time burning mechanism based on gas fees. A fixed ratio of the gas fee collected is burned in each block, with the ratio decided by BSC validators.

You buy long when you anticipated the value to rise. Short when you anticipated the value to fall.
Both can be leveraged, which means you increase your trading volume by that factor. It also means you'll narrow the margin as to when your trade will default in liquidation, which is a total loss. To avoid total loss, you can set Stop-loss prices at which your assets will be automatically sold (still a loss but not a complete one).
In both cases you're able to add liquidity to push your margin in which you want to trade.

Long: bet on rising prices - sell higher than you bought it for
Short: bet on falling prices - sell lower than you bought it for

Why can't this proof of reserves system use the private keys of the accounts which custody the coins to prove ownership over those addresses to cross reference against the stated total of custody?

Otherwise Binance is just shifting the trust from them to the 3rd party auditors.
private keys can't be shared, because u know... they're private
If you need help or you have an inquiry please ask your question in the #üÜò‚îÉcommunity-help channel

you wouldn't expose the private key, you would sign a message that can be used to prove that the private key associated with the public key signed that message, creating a proof that the private key for that address was accessible at the point in time the msg was signed, thus providing a pretty resilient proof that the funds are indeed backed 1:1 versus trusting the auditors which as we saw with FTX didn't mean much

You would just add up the funds stored in each of the accounts that have a proof of ownership and match that with the amount binance is advertising to see if it matches, if it does, then funds are backed 1:1

And if all cex's had to provide this then you could also ensure that 2 cex's aren't claiming the same wallet address as under their control. Providing further guarantees that everyone has control of their own separate funds, not rehypothecation.

Once a new IEO is announced, a snapshot is taken of potential investors‚Ä?BNB holdings over a set period that varies according to the sale. After the BNB holding period, a claim ticket button will appear for 24 hours to users which need to confirm their lottery tickets, after which the lottery will start and the winners will automatically allow users to become participants of the IEO in exchange for BNB tokens. How many tokens investors can keep depends on how much was committed overall, and is subject to individual caps."  Binance uses this lottery system to ensure that all the tokens that are offered reach as many people as reasonably possible.
